<div class="content-info">

<h3 class="title">

<span class="long-title">
Luke Skywalker
</span>
</h3>
<label class="alternative-name-label">Na'vi Name: </label><div class="alternative-name"></div>
<div class="desc-sizer" tabindex="-1">
<p class="desc">Luke Skywalker was a Tatooine farmboy who rose from humble beginnings to become one of the greatest Jedi the galaxy has ever known. Along with his friends Princess Leia and Han Solo, Luke battled the evil Empire, discovered the truth of his parentage, and ended the tyranny of the Sith. A generation later, the location of the famed Jedi master was one of the galaxy’s greatest mysteries. Haunted by Ben Solo’s fall to evil and convinced the Jedi had to end, Luke sought exile on a distant world, ignoring the galaxy’s pleas for help. But his solitude would be interrupted – and Luke Skywalker had one final, momentous role to play in the struggle between good and evil.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<section class="module header_banner no-bottom-padding header-left preserve-padding span-full-screen content-span-full-screen secondary-theme dark " id="ref-1-6">
<div class="bound">
<div class="module_header_container">
<div class="module_header">
<div class="title">
<h2 class="
base-color
title-container
module-cta-buttons
">
<span class="title-text">History</span>
<span class="title-buttons">
</span>
</h2>
</div>

</section><style type="text/css">

<!-- /* rich_text module 1-7 */ -->

</style>
<section class="module rich_text no-top-padding header-left preserve-padding secondary-theme dark " id="ref-1-7">

<div class="bound ">
<div class="rich-text-container">


<div class="rich_text_body rich-text-enabled">
<div class="rich-text-output" tabindex="0"><div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-hoqoq5_1496b98b.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C676" alt="Luke Skywalker on Tatooine" title="Luke Skywalker on Tatooine" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>Raised by his aunt and uncle on a <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/tatooine">Tatooine</a> <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/lars-moisture-farm">moisture farm</a>, Luke Skywalker never knew his mother or father. He knew nothing of the Force or Jedi, but longed for a more exciting life. Soon he would have it. With his Uncle Owen’s purchase of new droids <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/r2-d2">R2-D2</a> and <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/c-3po">C-3PO</a>, a chain of events was put in place that would change Luke -- and the galaxy -- forever. Artoo, a plucky astromech droid, wandered off in his first night on the farm, telling C-3PO he had to deliver a message to someone named <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/obi-wan-kenobi">Obi-Wan Kenobi</a>. When Luke went looking for the lost droid, he was attacked by <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/tusken-raiders">Tusken Raiders</a> and knocked unconscious. Before he could be taken captive, friendly hermit Ben Kenobi appeared and frightened off the Sand People. Ben revealed that he was indeed Obi-Wan Kenobi, and had something that belonged to Luke’s father: a <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/lightsaber">lightsaber</a>, the weapon of a Jedi. Obi-Wan said that he and Luke’s father were both Jedi Knights, strong with the Force, and good friends. Luke knew none of this, and asked how his father died. The old Jedi said that his former student, <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/darth-vader">Darth Vader,</a> turned to the dark side and killed him.</p><p>Obi-Wan and Luke soon discovered that Artoo was indeed carrying a message after all. It was a holorecording of <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/princess-leia-organa">Princess Leia</a>, stating that she had hidden stolen plans for the <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/galactic-empire">Empire</a>’s ultimate weapon, the<a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/death-star"> Death Star,</a> in the memory banks of Artoo; she asked that Kenobi deliver the plans to her father on <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/alderaan">Alderaan</a>. Obi-Wan implored Luke to come with him, but the farmboy refused. However, he and Obi-Wan found that the <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/jawa">Jawas</a> who sold his uncle Artoo and Threepio had been slaughtered by <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/stormtroopers">stormtroopers</a> -- and they may have traced them back home. Luke raced to the moisture farm, only to find the charred remains of his guardians. Stoic, he decided to leave Tatooine, vowing to learn the ways of the Force and become a Jedi like his father.</p><p>Along with hired pilot <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/han-solo">Han Solo</a> and his co-pilot and friend <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/chewbacca">Chewbacca,</a> Luke, Obi-Wan, and the droids headed for Alderaan aboard the <i><a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/millennium-falcon">Millennium Falcon</a></i>. But when they arrived, the planet wasn’t there -- only rubble, as it had been destroyed by the Empire’s Death Star. The <i>Falcon</i> was soon caught in the tractor beam of the giant space station, but it proved fortuitous; Princess Leia was being held there. Luke and Han, in stormtrooper disguises, staged a rescue while Obi-Wan disengaged the tractor beam. The Jedi Master, however, encountered his old student, Darth Vader, and was killed in battle. Luke saw it happen shortly before escaping in the <i>Falcon</i>, and was deeply affected by the loss of his mentor. <br></p><p>The small band of heroes regrouped with the<a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/rebel-alliance"> Rebel Alliance</a> on <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/yavin-4">Yavin 4</a>. With the Death Star plans successfully delivered, Luke joined the mission to destroy the battle station, piloting an <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/x-wing-starfighter">X-wing</a> under the call sign Red Five. In the ensuing battle, the Rebels suffered heavy losses, and Darth Vader entered the fray in his <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/darth-vader-s-tie-fighter">TIE Advanced</a>. One of the last remaining pilots, Luke flew through the Death Star trench at blinding speed with the goal of shooting a volley of proton torpedoes into a small exhaust port. Vader closed in, ready to destroy Luke's starship -- noting that “the Force is strong with this one” -- but a surprise blast from Han and the <i>Millennium Falcon</i> sent Vader's fighter tumbling into space, clearing Luke for the shot. Calling on the Force with guidance from Obi-Wan’s disembodied voice, the Jedi-to-be delivered a precise shot, and the Death Star was destroyed.</p>

<div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-18sx8vb_75ce646a.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C675" alt="Luke Skywalker training with Yoda on Dagobah" title="Luke Skywalker training with Yoda on Dagobah" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>Though the Rebel Alliance had struck a major blow against the Empire with the destruction of the Death Star, the war was far from over. The Alliance built a new secret base on the ice planet <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/hoth">Hoth</a>, with Luke now a commander. While out on patrol, Luke spotted what he thought was a meteor impact on the surface -- in reality, it was an<a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/imperial-probe-droid"> Imperial probe droid</a>. Before he could inspect it, however, Luke was viciously attacked by a towering <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/wampa">wampa</a>. Though Luke escaped the ice creature’s cave, severing the monster’s arm with his lightsaber, the young Jedi nearly died from the frigid surface temperatures. It was also at this time that he was visited by the spectre of Obi-Wan Kenobi, who instructed him to go to the <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/dagobah">Dagobah</a> system. There, he would learn the ways of the Force from <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/yoda">Yoda</a>, a Jedi Master. Han eventually found Luke, keeping him warm inside a <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/tauntaun">tauntaun</a>’s belly until help could arrive. Luke recovered from his injuries and lead the Rebel defense against the Empire’s ground forces, including massive <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/at-at-walker">AT-AT walkers</a>, giving the Alliance time to evacuate the planet.</p><p>Luke headed to Dagobah as instructed and found Yoda. He was not what Luke expected -- small, alien, and green, with a unique backwards way of speaking. Luke trained hard, failing often but learning much from his wise Master. During an exercise, the young Jedi saw a vision of his friends in pain; Luke cut his training short -- against Yoda's wishes -- to help them. He left for <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/cloud-city">Cloud City</a> where Darth Vader awaited, hoping to capture Luke and bring him to the<a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/emperor-palpatine-darth-sidious"> Emperor</a>. They dueled, but Luke was outmatched and overpowered. Luke was battered and bloodied in the fight, losing a hand, and the Sith Lord revealed a frightening truth: that he was in fact Luke’s father. Vader wanted his son to join him on the dark side, and together they could overthrow the Emperor and rule the galaxy. Luke was shattered and in disbelief. He refused to turn, managing to escape with his life.</p>

<div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-1ymefwb_483d5487.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C675" alt="Luke Skywalker as a Jedi Knight on Jabba's Sail Barge" title="Luke Skywalker as a Jedi Knight on Jabba's Sail Barge" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>With Han frozen in carbonite and held in <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/jabba-the-hutts-palace">Jabba the Hutt’s palace</a> on Tatooine, Luke led a mission to rescue his old friend. Now a powerful Jedi Knight, Luke tried to bargain for Han’s life but the crime lord refused. Through a trap door, he dispatched the Jedi into an underground dungeon and unleashed his massive <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/rancor">rancor</a> creature. But to the shock of <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/jabba-the-hutt">Jabba</a> and his henchmen, Luke was able to destroy the beast. Incensed, the gangster sentenced Luke and his friends to die in the <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/sarlacc">Sarlacc</a>, but again, the Jedi was underestimated. Luke decimated Jabba’s men, and the group of heroes completed their rescue.</p><p>With Han safe, Luke returned to Dagobah to complete his training. Yoda, however, was dying. In his final moments, the old Master told Luke that he required no more lessons, but he had to confront Darth Vader -- who was his true father -- once more. Yoda also told him of another Skywalker, who Obi-Wan would confirm was Leia, his twin sister.</p><p>Meanwhile, the Empire was constructing a new <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/death-star-ii">Death Star</a> -- with the Emperor personally overseeing its completion. Utilizing stolen schematics, the Rebel Alliance formulated a plan to destroy this new superweapon. Luke joined his friends for the mission on <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/endor">Endor</a>, but departed when he sensed Vader’s presence. Luke believed there was still good in his father, that the Emperor had not driven it from him fully. He tried to convert Vader to the light side, but the Dark Lord claimed it was too late. Instead, he brought Luke before the Emperor on the Death Star. The evil Sith Master looked to turn Luke to the dark side, and goaded him into a duel with his father. When Vader suggested that Leia could be turned to evil, Luke embraced his rage and pummeled his father relentlessly -- giving the Emperor exactly what he wanted. But before he delivered the killing blow, Luke paused, remembering his teachings. Calming himself, Luke threw away his weapon. “I am a Jedi, like my father before me,” he said. The Emperor, confounded by Luke’s actions, unleashed <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/force-lightning">Force lightning</a> upon the young Jedi. Vader rose and threw the Emperor down a deep shaft, his true self reawakened by his son’s love. Luke had one final moment with his father, and escaped the space station before it was destroyed. The once reckless farmboy’s journey was complete: he was a mature Jedi, freedom was restored to the galaxy, and his compassion had saved his father. </p><h4></h4>

<div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/luke-tfa-1-retina_ab8b72ba.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C503" alt="Luke Skywalker and R2-D2 after the destruction of his Jedi Academy" title="Luke Skywalker and R2-D2 after the destruction of his Jedi Academy" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>After the Battle of Endor, Luke traveled the galaxy with R2-D2, seeking long-forgotten Jedi lore as he pondered how to resurrect the Jedi order. But his efforts ended with one of his apprentices leaving his plans in ruin. After this tragedy Luke vanished, and no one knew where he had chosen to spend his self-imposed exile.</p>

<h4></h4>

<div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/luke-db-tlj_bcad54f1.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C500" alt="Luke Skywalker training Rey in the ways of the Force on Ahch-To" title="Luke Skywalker training Rey in the ways of the Force on Ahch-To" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>The scavenger <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/rey">Rey</a> tracked Luke down on <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/ahch-to">Ahch-To</a>, and pleaded with him to return and help the <a href="http://www.starwars.com/databank/the-resistance">Resistance</a>. Rey also needed his help to understand her burgeoning Force powers. Luke refused, telling her it was time for the Jedi to end. When Rey resisted refused to leave, Luke reluctantly agreed to teach her enough that she would understand why he had made his decision.</p>

<div class="media-image media-image-inline" style="text-align: center;">
<figure contenteditable="false">
<img src="https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/luke-skywalker-tlj-history-ahch-to-sunset_33f44de5.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C500" alt="Luke Skywalker performing Force projection from Ahch-To to Crait" title="Luke Skywalker performing Force projection from Ahch-To to Crait" data-alignment="" draggable="false">
</figure>
</div><p>Rey insisted that the galaxy needed the legend of Luke Skywalker, a plea that seemed to fall on deaf ears. She left <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/ahch-to">Ahch-To</a>, but Luke had opened himself to the Force – and a last lesson from his old master, <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/yoda">Yoda</a>. Luke projected himself through the Force to confront <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/kylo-ren">Kylo Ren</a> on <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/crait">Crait</a>, giving the <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/the-resistance">Resistance</a> a chance to escape the <a href="https://www.starwars.com/databank/the-first-order">First Order</a>. He passed into the Force, but his legend would continue to inspire the galaxy.</p><p></p><p></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

class=\"media-image media-image-inline\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\n \u003cfigure contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-hoqoq5_1496b98b.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C676\" alt=\"Luke Skywalker on Tatooine\" title=\"Luke Skywalker on Tatooine\" data-alignment=\"\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eRaised by his aunt and uncle on a \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/tatooine\"\u003eTatooine\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/lars-moisture-farm\"\u003emoisture farm\u003c/a\u003e, Luke Skywalker never knew his mother or father. He knew nothing of the Force or Jedi, but longed for a more exciting life. Soon he would have it. With his Uncle Owen’s purchase of new droids \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/r2-d2\"\u003eR2-D2\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/c-3po\"\u003eC-3PO\u003c/a\u003e, a chain of events was put in place that would change Luke -- and the galaxy -- forever. Artoo, a plucky astromech droid, wandered off in his first night on the farm, telling C-3PO he had to deliver a message to someone named \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/obi-wan-kenobi\"\u003eObi-Wan Kenobi\u003c/a\u003e. When Luke went looking for the lost droid, he was attacked by \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/tusken-raiders\"\u003eTusken Raiders\u003c/a\u003e and knocked unconscious. Before he could be taken captive, friendly hermit Ben Kenobi appeared and frightened off the Sand People. Ben revealed that he was indeed Obi-Wan Kenobi, and had something that belonged to Luke’s father: a \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/lightsaber\"\u003elightsaber\u003c/a\u003e, the weapon of a Jedi. Obi-Wan said that he and Luke’s father were both Jedi Knights, strong with the Force, and good friends. Luke knew none of this, and asked how his father died. The old Jedi said that his former student, \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/darth-vader\"\u003eDarth Vader,\u003c/a\u003e turned to the dark side and killed him.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eObi-Wan and Luke soon discovered that Artoo was indeed carrying a message after all. It was a holorecording of \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/princess-leia-organa\"\u003ePrincess Leia\u003c/a\u003e, stating that she had hidden stolen plans for the \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/galactic-empire\"\u003eEmpire\u003c/a\u003e’s ultimate weapon, the\u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/death-star\"\u003e Death Star,\u003c/a\u003e in the memory banks of Artoo; she asked that Kenobi deliver the plans to her father on \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/alderaan\"\u003eAlderaan\u003c/a\u003e. Obi-Wan implored Luke to come with him, but the farmboy refused. However, he and Obi-Wan found that the \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/jawa\"\u003eJawas\u003c/a\u003e who sold his uncle Artoo and Threepio had been slaughtered by \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/stormtroopers\"\u003estormtroopers\u003c/a\u003e -- and they may have traced them back home. Luke raced to the moisture farm, only to find the charred remains of his guardians. Stoic, he decided to leave Tatooine, vowing to learn the ways of the Force and become a Jedi like his father.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlong with hired pilot \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/han-solo\"\u003eHan Solo\u003c/a\u003e and his co-pilot and friend \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/chewbacca\"\u003eChewbacca,\u003c/a\u003e Luke, Obi-Wan, and the droids headed for Alderaan aboard the \u003ci\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/millennium-falcon\"\u003eMillennium Falcon\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/i\u003e. But when they arrived, the planet wasn’t there -- only rubble, as it had been destroyed by the Empire’s Death Star. The \u003ci\u003eFalcon\u003c/i\u003e was soon caught in the tractor beam of the giant space station, but it proved fortuitous; Princess Leia was being held there. Luke and Han, in stormtrooper disguises, staged a rescue while Obi-Wan disengaged the tractor beam. The Jedi Master, however, encountered his old student, Darth Vader, and was killed in battle. Luke saw it happen shortly before escaping in the \u003ci\u003eFalcon\u003c/i\u003e, and was deeply affected by the loss of his mentor. \u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe small band of heroes regrouped with the\u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/rebel-alliance\"\u003e Rebel Alliance\u003c/a\u003e on \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/yavin-4\"\u003eYavin 4\u003c/a\u003e. With the Death Star plans successfully delivered, Luke joined the mission to destroy the battle station, piloting an \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/x-wing-starfighter\"\u003eX-wing\u003c/a\u003e under the call sign Red Five. In the ensuing battle, the Rebels suffered heavy losses, and Darth Vader entered the fray in his \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/darth-vader-s-tie-fighter\"\u003eTIE Advanced\u003c/a\u003e. One of the last remaining pilots, Luke flew through the Death Star trench at blinding speed with the goal of shooting a volley of proton torpedoes into a small exhaust port. Vader closed in, ready to destroy Luke's starship -- noting that “the Force is strong with this one” -- but a surprise blast from Han and the \u003ci\u003eMillennium Falcon\u003c/i\u003e sent Vader's fighter tumbling into space, clearing Luke for the shot. Calling on the Force with guidance from Obi-Wan’s disembodied voice, the Jedi-to-be delivered a precise shot, and the Death Star was destroyed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"media-image media-image-inline\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\n \u003cfigure contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-18sx8vb_75ce646a.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C675\" alt=\"Luke Skywalker training with Yoda on Dagobah\" title=\"Luke Skywalker training with Yoda on Dagobah\" data-alignment=\"\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThough the Rebel Alliance had struck a major blow against the Empire with the destruction of the Death Star, the war was far from over. The Alliance built a new secret base on the ice planet \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/hoth\"\u003eHoth\u003c/a\u003e, with Luke now a commander. While out on patrol, Luke spotted what he thought was a meteor impact on the surface -- in reality, it was an\u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/imperial-probe-droid\"\u003e Imperial probe droid\u003c/a\u003e. Before he could inspect it, however, Luke was viciously attacked by a towering \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/wampa\"\u003ewampa\u003c/a\u003e. Though Luke escaped the ice creature’s cave, severing the monster’s arm with his lightsaber, the young Jedi nearly died from the frigid surface temperatures. It was also at this time that he was visited by the spectre of Obi-Wan Kenobi, who instructed him to go to the \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/dagobah\"\u003eDagobah\u003c/a\u003e system. There, he would learn the ways of the Force from \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/yoda\"\u003eYoda\u003c/a\u003e, a Jedi Master. Han eventually found Luke, keeping him warm inside a \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/tauntaun\"\u003etauntaun\u003c/a\u003e’s belly until help could arrive. Luke recovered from his injuries and lead the Rebel defense against the Empire’s ground forces, including massive \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/at-at-walker\"\u003eAT-AT walkers\u003c/a\u003e, giving the Alliance time to evacuate the planet.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eLuke headed to Dagobah as instructed and found Yoda. He was not what Luke expected -- small, alien, and green, with a unique backwards way of speaking. Luke trained hard, failing often but learning much from his wise Master. During an exercise, the young Jedi saw a vision of his friends in pain; Luke cut his training short -- against Yoda's wishes -- to help them. He left for \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/cloud-city\"\u003eCloud City\u003c/a\u003e where Darth Vader awaited, hoping to capture Luke and bring him to the\u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/emperor-palpatine-darth-sidious\"\u003e Emperor\u003c/a\u003e. They dueled, but Luke was outmatched and overpowered. Luke was battered and bloodied in the fight, losing a hand, and the Sith Lord revealed a frightening truth: that he was in fact Luke’s father. Vader wanted his son to join him on the dark side, and together they could overthrow the Emperor and rule the galaxy. Luke was shattered and in disbelief. He refused to turn, managing to escape with his life.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"media-image media-image-inline\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\n \u003cfigure contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/open-uri20150608-27674-1ymefwb_483d5487.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C675\" alt=\"Luke Skywalker as a Jedi Knight on Jabba's Sail Barge\" title=\"Luke Skywalker as a Jedi Knight on Jabba's Sail Barge\" data-alignment=\"\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith Han frozen in carbonite and held in \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/jabba-the-hutts-palace\"\u003eJabba the Hutt’s palace\u003c/a\u003e on Tatooine, Luke led a mission to rescue his old friend. Now a powerful Jedi Knight, Luke tried to bargain for Han’s life but the crime lord refused. Through a trap door, he dispatched the Jedi into an underground dungeon and unleashed his massive \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/rancor\"\u003erancor\u003c/a\u003e creature. But to the shock of \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/jabba-the-hutt\"\u003eJabba\u003c/a\u003e and his henchmen, Luke was able to destroy the beast. Incensed, the gangster sentenced Luke and his friends to die in the \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/sarlacc\"\u003eSarlacc\u003c/a\u003e, but again, the Jedi was underestimated. Luke decimated Jabba’s men, and the group of heroes completed their rescue.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith Han safe, Luke returned to Dagobah to complete his training. Yoda, however, was dying. In his final moments, the old Master told Luke that he required no more lessons, but he had to confront Darth Vader -- who was his true father -- once more. Yoda also told him of another Skywalker, who Obi-Wan would confirm was Leia, his twin sister.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMeanwhile, the Empire was constructing a new \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/death-star-ii\"\u003eDeath Star\u003c/a\u003e -- with the Emperor personally overseeing its completion. Utilizing stolen schematics, the Rebel Alliance formulated a plan to destroy this new superweapon. Luke joined his friends for the mission on \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/endor\"\u003eEndor\u003c/a\u003e, but departed when he sensed Vader’s presence. Luke believed there was still good in his father, that the Emperor had not driven it from him fully. He tried to convert Vader to the light side, but the Dark Lord claimed it was too late. Instead, he brought Luke before the Emperor on the Death Star. The evil Sith Master looked to turn Luke to the dark side, and goaded him into a duel with his father. When Vader suggested that Leia could be turned to evil, Luke embraced his rage and pummeled his father relentlessly -- giving the Emperor exactly what he wanted. But before he delivered the killing blow, Luke paused, remembering his teachings. Calming himself, Luke threw away his weapon. “I am a Jedi, like my father before me,” he said. The Emperor, confounded by Luke’s actions, unleashed \u003ca href=\"http://www.starwars.com/databank/force-lightning\"\u003eForce lightning\u003c/a\u003e upon the young Jedi. Vader rose and threw the Emperor down a deep shaft, his true self reawakened by his son’s love. Luke had one final moment with his father, and escaped the space station before it was destroyed. The once reckless farmboy’s journey was complete: he was a mature Jedi, freedom was restored to the galaxy, and his compassion had saved his father. \u003c/p\u003e\u003ch4\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"media-image media-image-inline\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\n \u003cfigure contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/luke-tfa-1-retina_ab8b72ba.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C1200%2C503\" alt=\"Luke Skywalker and R2-D2 after the destruction of his Jedi Academy\" title=\"Luke Skywalker and R2-D2 after the destruction of his Jedi Academy\" data-alignment=\"\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\n \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eAfter the Battle of Endor, Luke traveled the galaxy with R2-D2, seeking long-forgotten Jedi lore as he pondered how to resurrect the Jedi order. Rey also needed his help to understand her burgeoning Force powers. Luke refused, telling her it was time for the Jedi to end. Decades later, continuing the power of two in \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, Leia’s son Ben Solo discovers he is part of a powerful Force dyad with a scavenger named Rey. While Ben and Rey are not twins, or related by blood, they share a unique bond that bridges the minds of the duo, connecting them across space and time.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"media-image\" style=\"text-align: center; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/mikkian_8a340cde_0c612247.jpeg?region=0,0,1560,666\" alt=\"Tiplee and Tiplar\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAnother set of twin Jedi appeared in the animated series \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/series/star-wars-the-clone-wars\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars: The Clone Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e. \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/databank/tiplee\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTiplee\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e and \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/databank/tiplar\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTiplar\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, Mikkian twins, were both Jedi generals during the Clone Wars. Fighting as a unified front, Tiplee and Tiplar are a rare example of Jedi who were not separated from their entire family as children. Their connection and attachment to each other takes a tragic turn in the episode “The Unknown,” when Clone Trooper Tup’s inhibitor chip malfunctions leading him to prematurely execute Order 66 and assassinate Tiplar in battle. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eGrieving the loss of her sister, Tiplee must fight some very un-Jedi-like emotions to keep her from seeking revenge. The loss of a twin also played a role in the comic series \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eBounty Hunters\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e \u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003ewhere former bounty hunter T’onga leaves her peaceful life as a farmer behind to return to the underworld to avenge the death of her twin brother, T’ongor.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"media-image\" style=\"text-align: center; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/the-twins-main_ec3e8568.jpeg?region=0,0,1280,539\" alt=\"The Twins\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/series/star-wars-visions\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars: Visions\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e canon-adjacent short “The Twins” focuses on twin siblings created through the power of the dark side. Master Am and Master Karre both wear armor refined with dark energy that threatens to power a planet-destroying weapon. While Master Am is prepared to sacrifice her body if necessary to make this dark power a reality to fight the Republic, her brother Karre revolts from his planned destiny, stealing the weapon’s kyber crystal power core. The twins battle each other; as one sees a chance for power, the other sees only despair. Ultimately, Karre turns to the power of the light side of the Force to try and stop his sister’s plan — as well as save her life.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"media-image\" style=\"text-align: center; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/the-twins-the-book-of-boba-fett-quote_560ef801.jpeg?region=0,0,1280,720\" alt=\"The Twins in The Book of Boba Fett\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSome \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003e siblings work closely together while other duos are literally connected to each other. A\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e pair of Hutt twins, known simply as \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/databank/the-twins\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ethe Twins\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, try to lay claim to their cousin Jabba the Hutt’s territory during the New Republic era in \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/series/the-book-of-boba-fett\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eThe Book of Boba Fett\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e episode \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/series/the-book-of-boba-fett/chapter-2-tribes-of-tatooine-episode-guide\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e“The Tribes of Tatooine.”\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e The brother and sister Hutt make an indelible impression as they’re carried on an enormous litter through the streets of Mos Espa with a personal drummer to signal their arrival. And while not technically twins, \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003e stories have also featured some peculiar twin-headed characters. The talkative two-headed Troig Fode and Beed appeared in \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eThe Phantom Menace\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003e and the Danzikan Lark and Jonk can be found in \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/films/solo\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eSolo: A Star Wars Story\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDuring \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/the-high-republic\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ethe High Republic era\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, about a hundred years before the events of \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.starwars.com/series/the-acolyte\" class=\"editor-link\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eThe Acolyte\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, Jedi bond-twins Terec and Ceret assisted the Jedi Order in their battle against the deadly and carnivorous Drengir and violent Nihil marauders. As bond-twins, Terec and Ceret’s connection is unique. The twins share the same mind, can sense each other’s thoughts, and are affected when the other is injured or in pain. While not physically connected, the Kotabi siblings in many ways share the same life experience — even able to help their sibling heal despite a long physical separation.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"media-image\" style=\"text-align: center; max-width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" contenteditable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/the-acolyte-twins-mae-osha_584a2040.jpeg?region=0,0,1280,854\" alt=\"A young Osha and Mae\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMany mysteries remain about Osha and Mae’s creation, but their existence appears unique in the \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e \u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003egalaxy: as Torbin discovered through a blood sample analysis, the girls are biologically the same person, essentially one consciousness split into two bodies. Created by Mother Aniseya’s witch coven, whose chants allude to “the power of two” the girl’s bond as young children is clear, as evidenced in their call-and-response rhyme\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e “Always one, but born as two. As above sits the stars, and below lies the sea. I give you you. And you give me me.” While Mae finds comfort and meaning in these words, Osha seems to feel trapped and limited. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe siblings find themselves at a dangerous crossroad after Osha tells her mothers she wants to become a Jedi, instead of remaining with their witch coven alongside Mae, a choice that quite literally sparks the events of the series beginning with the fire at the fortress. Both Mae and Osha remain filled with mixed feelings of grief and blame, but their bond remains clear when they are reunited years later.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"editor-paragraph\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEvery \u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003e\u003cem class=\"editor-text-italic\"\u003eStar Wars\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cspan\u003e story is defined by the connections characters have to one another - whether these connections are by blood, shared history, or common goals. Calrissian.\u003c/h2\u003e","main_content":"\u003cp\u003eIt's like something from a dream.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eJedi Master Luke Skywalker is haunted by visions of the dark side, foretelling an ominous secret growing somewhere in the depths of space, on a dead world called Exegol. The disturbance in the Force is undeniable and Luke’s worst fears are confirmed when his old friend Lando Calrissian comes to him with reports of a new Sith menace.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eToday, StarWars.com is pleased to reveal the cover of the forthcoming novel \u003ca href=\"https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/678693/star-wars-shadow-of-the-sith-by-adam-christopher/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eStar Wars: Shadow of the Sith\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, tracing Luke and Lando's quest to find Exegol in a story set between the events of \u003cem\u003eStar Wars: Return of the Jedi\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003eStar Wars: The Force Awakens \u003c/em\u003eand featuring Ochi of Bestoon, the Sith assassin first introduced in \u003cem\u003eStar Wars: The Rise of Skywalker\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe novel arrives this summer, but today you can read StarWars.com's first excerpt from the forthcoming title following Luke's impossible journey from the seeing stone on Tython to the ashy Sith world...\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_8d0cd52d.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"size-full wp-image-183374 aligncenter\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_8d0cd52d.jpeg\" alt=\"Luke and Lando on the cover of Star Wars: Shadow of the Sith.\" width=\"658\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThere was a bang, more like a thunderclap, and everything went black. The breeze dropped, the air still and warm. Luke took a breath and could taste dry dust on his tongue, and then he realized he wasn’t sitting on the seeing stone anymore. Tython was gone. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHe looked down. He was \u003ci\u003estanding\u003c/i\u003e now on black dirt, hard-packed, cracked, coated with dust that swirled in eddies around his boots.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHe looked up. The world was black and dry, the sky dark and filled with roiling black clouds, lit by constant flashes of lightning that shorted directly down into the ground. If it was day or night, Luke couldn’t tell -- the place was both light and dark at the same time, the vast, flat plain of black stone lit evenly from a sun that wasn’t there.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke took another breath, the taste getting stronger in his mouth. Already his eyes were drying out, the atmosphere, the ground, the whole place so old, so desiccated.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHe knew immediately where he was. He had been here many times recently, this nightmare landscape of his visions.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eOnly now he knew its name.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThis was Exegol, the hidden world of Sith only whispered about in ancient texts. A place reachable only with a wayfinder.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnd… by meditation? Luke took a step forward, finding the ground solid and most definitely real under his feet. He walked a small and slow circle, eyes at the horizon. Lightning flashed, lighting the farther reaches of the plain, revealing it to be featureless and dead.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe same place as his visions, yes, but this felt… different.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThis felt \u003ci\u003ereal\u003c/i\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eCould he have been transported? Luke frowned, his mind racing along with his heart. True enough, he didn’t know the full extent of the powers of the seeing stone. He had researched the place for years, but he had never actually used the stone for its ancient purpose, to commune directly with the Force. He knew himself what a powerful Jedi he had become, what untapped potential he still had within himself despite -- or perhaps because of -- his years of self-directed, Masterless training.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHad he done it? He had the holocron, or what was left of it, and the kyber crystals. Was there enough of the holocron data core left for the seeing stone to have been able to read it, somehow, taking him to where the original owner had failed to reach, all those centuries ago? And what about the kyber crystals? They resonated with the Force, their very structures in a natural, sympathetic vibration with it. Were they the catalyst, making the journey possible? Was that what the original pilot had tried -- combining two very different forms of Sith power to overcome their lack of a true wayfinder?\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt was then that a far more important question entered Luke’s head.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eCould he get back to Tython?\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThen he spun, ducking instinctively as something brushed past the hood of his robe, strong enough to shift the heavy fabric over his shoulder. There was nobody behind him. He turned the circle again. He was alone on the plain, the air perfectly still, the caustic sour taste growing ever stronger in his mouth.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAgain. Something brushing past him, this time with a distinct \u003ci\u003ewhoosh\u003c/i\u003e of the dry air and the sound of someone’s feet scraping along the hard ground. Luke ducked out of the way again, moving a few meters from his original position. Looking down he saw his footprints in the dust -- it was hardly an impression, but enough for him to see his own tracks.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnd the tracks of someone, or something, else. Two large arcs, not footsteps but the signs of something being dragged along the ground, on opposite sides of where Luke had just been standing.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHe looked up, turning slowly to see all around him. There was no place to hide—no rocks, no buildings, nothing. Luke could see from horizon to empty horizon.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLightning flashed and then he saw it, just for an instant as it was lit up by the electrical storm. A figure, a fair distance away, perhaps one hundred meters. And then it was gone, before Luke could register any features or form at all.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e“Hello?” he called out, feeling slightly foolish. He tried again. “Who’s there?”\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAgain the sound, louder now, and he felt something physically push his back. He went with the movement to keep his own footing, moved forward farther, then spun around, his hand whipping his lightsaber from his belt and presenting it in one smooth, fluid movement. He paused, feet spread, weight low, the defensive position that was as instinctive, as automatic, for him as breathing.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke was surrounded. They were tall, thin. Nine of them. Nothing more than wraiths. Nothing more than shadows. Tall, thin ghosts, their bodies curved and arced in a new wind that had picked up, a wind that gusted across the black plain, changing direction constantly.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke adjusted his grip on his lightsaber and thumbed the activator. With a searing \u003ci\u003eswoosh\u003c/i\u003e, the green blade ignited, illuminating a large circle around Luke and the wraiths, lighting the ashy dust that swirled in the air like a halo.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke braced himself. Because these weren’t ghosts or shadows or wraiths. They were very real. With each flash of lightning in the dark sky above, the wraiths were lit as solid, three-dimensional figures, black-robed, bandage-faced.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt was disorienting. Luke narrowed his eyes as he focused, the foes surrounding him flashing between translucent billowing shadows and solid humanoid figures.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThen they began to circle him. They kept the same distance from Luke, and from one\u003cspan class=\"Apple-converted-space\"\u003e  \u003c/span\u003eanother, as they moved, all of them keeping their front facing this intruder into their world. Luke, balanced on the balls of his feet, fingers adjusting, readjusting on the grip of his lightsaber, was ready for the attack he knew was coming, all the while his mind racing.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eHow did I get here… and how do I get back?\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnd then the wraiths, moving in unison as though some unseen, unheard communication had passed among them, reached into robes that were in one instant eddies of ash and in the next flash of lightning a heavy, woven black textile, and pulled out lightsabers of their own.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke, with his years of experience, years of learning to master his emotions and control his actions, did not allow the sight of these nine weapons to surprise him. Because… of course they had lightsabers. He was on Exegol, the Sith world, the heart of darkness. He had dared to see into the planet with the Force, and was now here, in physical reality, facing nine embodiments of the dark side who clearly wanted their existence to remain hidden.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe wraiths lifted their lightsabers and activated them. Luke didn’t so much hear their ignition as feel it inside, the familiar sound somehow high-pitched and distant, a half-forgotten memory rather than an actual physical sensation. The wraiths lifted their blades, ready to meet Luke’s, but they were nothing, mere black outlines against the black figures standing on the black ground under a black sky. But when the lightning flashed, the nine blades were inverted, a negative flash of white that made spots dance in Luke’s eyes. Dazzled, Luke’s control slipped for just a moment, and he took an involuntary half step backward.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt was what the wraiths had been waiting for. They rushed at him in silence, their robes of shadow-ash disintegrating in the wind as they moved, their whole bodies becoming insubstantial, particulate matter that blew away in the breeze. And then the lightning flashed and Luke was surrounded by nine very real, very solid, black-clad figures swinging lightsabers of blinding, impossible light.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eDriven by instinct, guided by his connection to the Force, Luke parried the first blows, his lightsaber connecting with his enemies’ with a familiar high-energy splash. But with the lightning flashing along with the nine black-white blades of his enemies, Luke soon found he that he was, effectively, fighting blind, his vision nothing but purple spots and red smears.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eBut Luke Skywalker did not panic, did not fear. Deflecting another attack, Luke closed his eyes and let out a breath. He didn’t need eyes to see his enemies. All he had to do was look \u003ci\u003einward\u003c/i\u003e, to feel the Force flow through him, to feel its connection with himself, and the galaxy, and all the beings that lived within.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eI am one with the Force, and the Force is with me.\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe next attack was parried with perfection; Luke’s riposte was likewise a textbook example of the Jedi form.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eBut then his blade passed through… nothing.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke didn’t open his eyes, he just bowed his head, spinning on the spot to counter the attacks coming from the other side while he concentrated, trying to enter an almost meditative state so he could press an attack rather than let the Force guide him merely through a passive, automatic defense.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnd then he faltered. A frown flickered across his face as he reached out with the Force and…\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThere was nothing. No connection. No feeling. It was as though he was still on Tython, on the seeing stone, at the center of a grace where the Force coalesced around him but not \u003ci\u003ewithin\u003c/i\u003e him.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe beings around him, nine shadow wraiths with blades of light and dark, did not exist in the Force -- they had no presence, no form.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThis was impossible.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe Force connected all life in the galaxy, but it also surrounded and penetrated the inanimate. Objects -- rocks, planets, starships, droids, everything -- had a presence in the Force, or rather, an \u003ci\u003eabsence\u003c/i\u003e that could be felt as strongly as if they were living things themselves.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eBut the wraiths were nothing. Luke couldn’t sense them with the Force at all.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHe turned left then right, lightsaber swinging up, then down, then out, parrying three more blows. But blinded and unable to even sense his opponents, he was unable to attack. He might as well just be swinging randomly at the air around him.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eWhich he did. He opened his eyes, squinting against the flashes of lightning and the searing sweeps of the wraith-blades, his own green lightsaber the one thing that was familiar, the only color in his nightmare.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eBut that faithful lightsaber could do nothing against the wraiths. He blocked a blow -- his eyes and brain beginning to adjust, very slightly, to the disorienting world around him -- and then came in with an attack, high and then low, completely avoiding his opponent’s blade. But his lightsaber passed through the wraith, dragging a wake of ash behind it, lit in the glowing green of Luke’s laser sword.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe wraith didn’t even seem to notice. It brought its blade up and Luke parried, parried again, ducked sideways and parried a blow from his left side, swung the lightsaber to the right to counter another, then carved a series of angled attacks that should have cut the three opponents in front of him to ribbons.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eHis blade met no resistance -- on the contrary, the wraith directly in front of him stepped \u003ci\u003einto\u003c/i\u003e his attack, apparently unaware or unconcerned as to the position of Luke’s blade.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke didn’t stop moving. He dodged the shadow-blade of the wraith even as he passed \u003ci\u003ethrough\u003c/i\u003e the being himself, the cloud of ash and dust thick around his face, coating his skin, his tongue, filling his mouth with the taste of hot metal. Now behind the group, he turned, and pressed a fresh attack to their rear, swinging his lightsaber left and right and left again, blocking the thrust of a shadow-blade as one wraith turned in a whirlwind of spinning black smoke and brought its weapon to bear. Once again, lightsaber met lightsaber, green light met shadow-blade, and Luke could feel the jolt through the hilt of his own weapon, could see the fizz of energy as his blade slid along the length of his enemy’s, before the wraith pulled away in one direction and Luke in the other, both then turning to cut in at a sharp angle. Blade met blade again, this time with a bang of spitting plasma, as though the wraiths were toying with him, one moment their weapons real, the next, a shadowed imitation of reality.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eSensing this change, Luke’s next blow was powerful enough to knock the other blade away, and he quickly made his riposte, straight through the neck and torso of the apparition.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eOnce again, his blade met nothing. The shadow-form parted like smoke, even as lightning flashed again and the being was as solid as Luke’s own body.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke swung again, and again, and again, sweeping now with his blade with no particular intent or design except to keep the nine wraiths at a distance, his focus now not on the fight but on figuring a way \u003ci\u003eout\u003c/i\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe wraiths pressed their attack, Luke’s blade passing harmlessly through them. As they got closer and closer, they raised their own lightsabers again, acting together in telepathic union, ready to make their final strike.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eNine blades against one. Luke didn’t like the odds, but he braced himself nonetheless.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe wraiths attacked, nine shadow-blades held by shadow-arms cutting down at speed --\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnd that was when a new light appeared. Not the white flash of lightning, or the wraith blades as they were lit by the unholy light. Not the green glow of Luke’s lightsaber, illuminating the ashy ground like a green flashlight.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eNo, this light was pale blue. It shimmered in the air, streaking a little it swept down, throwing the attackers off in one smooth movement.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt was a lightsaber, the blade blue and strong, the hilt --\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe hilt was transparent, nothing but a blue glow, held in a transparent blue hand.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke fell backward, onto his elbows, and gasped at the pain in his joints and also in sheer surprise at the sight before him.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eStanding between himself and the wraiths was another figure—a man in flowing pale robes, his back to Luke, his head hidden under a voluminous hood. The entire figure glowed like soft electricity, bright in this world of endless night. When the lightning flashed, Luke could see the nine solid wraiths through the form of the man who stood between them and their quarry.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke’s mind raced as he tried to identify the spirit of the Force who had arrived to protect him.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e“Ben?”\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eNo, it wasn’t Ben… the robe, the man’s form, was --\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe spectral being lifted his lightsaber, holding it high above his head, the blade parallel to the ground.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eFor the first time, the wraiths seemed to take note of their enemy. They backed away, nine forms huddling together, blades lowered. They were screaming from their blank bandaged faces, although Luke wasn’t sure whether it was a real sound or just an echo inside his head. It was hard to concentrate on what he was seeing, the way the Force reverberated around the figure in blue. His entire vision seemed to buckle around him.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe wraiths continued to back away, and then they vanished, their shadow-shapes evaporating into dust that spun away on the last eddy of the dying wind.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eFor a moment, all was still.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThen the blue figure turned around, his lightsaber extinguished.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke pushed himself up onto his elbows. He blinked.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt couldn’t be.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eIt \u003ci\u003ecouldn’t\u003c/i\u003e be.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eThe blue figure lifted his hood back to reveal the strong, sharp face of a young man, his gaze intense beneath a furrowed brow that was bisected by straight, vertical scar. His thick hair was shoulder-length and had a slight wave to it.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eAnakin Skywalker reached out his hand.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\"p1\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003eLuke took it, and everything went white.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/678693/star-wars-shadow-of-the-sith-by-adam-christopher/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePre-order \u003c/em\u003eStar Wars: Shadow of the Sith\u003c/a\u003e \u003cem\u003eby Adam Christopher\u003c/em\u003e \u003cem\u003ebefore it arrives June 28, 2022.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLearn more about this and other news in the latest episode of \u003cem\u003eThis Week! they see as the most impactful moment in the sequels.\u003c/h2\u003e","main_content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eOne of the great things about \u003c/em\u003eStar Wars\u003cem\u003e is that it inspires endless debates and opinions on a wide array of topics. Best bounty hunter? Most powerful Jedi? Does Salacious Crumb have the best haircut in the saga? In that spirit, StarWars.com presents From a Certain Point of View: a series of point-counterpoints on some of the biggest — and most fun — \u003c/em\u003eStar Wars\u003cem\u003e issues. In this installment, two StarWars.com writers take a stand on the most powerful moment in the \u003c/em\u003esequel trilogy -- Star Wars: The Force Awakens, Star Wars: The Last Jedi, and Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker --\u003cem\u003e now streaming on \u003ca href=\"https://disneyplus.com/?cid=DTCI-Synergy-StarWars-Site-Acquisition-StarWars-US-DisneyPlus-NA-EN-BlogArticleEmbed-Most-Memorable-Clone-Wars-Arc-NA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eDisney+\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_46686835.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-172136\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_46686835.jpeg\" alt=\"Rey’s confrontation with Palpatine on Exegol\" width=\"1280\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRey’s confrontation with Palpatine on Exegol is the most powerful moment in the latest trilogy, says Emily.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe arc Rey goes through from the beginning to the end of the sequel trilogy is perfectly captured in her confrontation with Palpatine. As Palpatine strikes lightning at his estranged granddaughter, Rey uses Leia’s lightsaber to withhold the overwhelming power coming from him. Palpatine claims, “I am \u003cem\u003eall\u003c/em\u003e the Sith.” And Rey, while using the Force to pull Luke’s saber to her free hand, confirms, “And I… I’m all the Jedi.” With both lightsabers, the lightning deflects right back at Palpatine until he’s nothing more than dust.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_66b984b3.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-162624\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_66b984b3.jpeg\" alt=\"Rey in Maz's castle\" width=\"1280\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo understand just how powerful this moment is, we have to go back to where Rey started. When we first met this humble scavenger in \u003cem\u003eStar Wars:\u003c/em\u003e \u003cem\u003eThe Force Awakens\u003c/em\u003e, Rey specifically told Maz, “I don’t want any part of this,” while \u003cem\u003erefusing\u003c/em\u003e to take Luke’s lightsaber that called to her on Takodana. At that point, Rey made her priorities clear; she just wanted to get back to Jakku to wait for her family to return. Of course, things didn’t go to plan and when she was faced with fighting Kylo Ren on Starkiller Base, she summoned the lightsaber to her hand using the Force, her first step in accepting her place with the Resistance, although she still had many questions and much to learn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat led Rey to her next destination: Ahch-To. After helping the Resistance recover the map to Luke Skywalker in the hopes that he’d be able to help them, Rey traveled to the Unknown Regions to retrieve the fabled Jedi master in \u003cem\u003eStar Wars: \u003c/em\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe Last Jedi\u003c/em\u003e. When she arrived, Rey was insistent that she was there because Leia sent her and that the Resistance needed his help. It wasn’t until Luke questioned her that she opened up. “I need someone to show me my place in all this,” she told him. Despite Kylo Ren’s attempt to convince her that she has “no place in this story,” and that she’s, “no one” -- but not to him, I know – she ultimately succeeded in discovering who she was.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_879942e4.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-172137\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_879942e4.jpeg\" alt=\"Rey on Exegol\" width=\"1280\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhich brings us back to \u003cem\u003eThe Rise of Skywalker \u003c/em\u003eand the final battle. Rey stands her ground against the most evil being in the galaxy, uses the lightsaber she once refused, and confirms her place in the story. Rey \u003cem\u003eis\u003c/em\u003e all the Jedi. And with that, her arc is complete.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_f0cef2cd.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-172135\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_f0cef2cd.jpeg\" alt=\"Luke Skywalker’s final duel with Kylo Ren\" width=\"1200\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIt’s Luke Skywalker’s final duel with Kylo Ren, says Dan.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs the modern mythology, \u003cem\u003eStar Wars \u003c/em\u003eis well known for evoking the pathos within so many of us, which is one of the reasons we continually come back for more. And while there are many powerful moments to choose from in the sequel trilogy, there can only be one winner, and naturally, it’s from the hero that started it all: Luke Skywalker.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt the end of \u003cem\u003eThe Force Awakens\u003c/em\u003e, we learn that Luke is hiding out on the mysterious planet Ahch-To, in a self-imposed exile, to essentially contemplate his existence and reinvent himself. His perceived failure with his nephew, Ben Solo, has left him bereft of hope, which is something altogether unexpected. How can one of the greatest heroes have given up on himself and the galaxy?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_9d7b2701.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-172134\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_9d7b2701.jpeg\" alt=\"Luke on Crait\" width=\"1280\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe short answer: He’s human. Even though Luke is arguably one of the most powerful Jedi in history, he is still a mere mortal. Yes, Luke has accomplished so much and saved so many. His Jedi skills are staggering and he did help redeem his father to the light side of the Force. He’s not perfect, but that just makes him more relatable. If the best of us can have doubts and make mistakes, it gives the rest of us hope that it’s OK to mess up or feel lost. The farm boy from Tatooine seems to have temporarily forgotten that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut, that’s not the end of Luke’s story. It’s just one chapter in an epic volume that culminates with perhaps the ultimate sacrifice: Luke’s triumphant return on Crait. With John Williams’ sweeping, “The Spark,” building to a crescendo, Luke Skywalker reunites with his sister, Leia, winks at C-3PO, and goes to face down the First Order all by himself. Unphased by the firepower of a line-up of AT-M6 walkers, with one casual flick to remove any dust from his shoulder, Luke Skywalker lets it be known that he is back to light the spark of hope for the Resistance and the galaxy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_01203601.jpeg\"\u003e\u003cimg class=\"aligncenter wp-image-155822\" src=\"https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/image_01203601.jpeg\" alt=\"Luke in The Last Jedi\" width=\"1280\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the beginning, Luke Skywalker has been a beacon of hope for generations of \u003cem\u003eStar Wars \u003c/em\u003efans. When we learn that Luke Force-projected himself across the galaxy, knowing full well he would die from the incredible strain, it amplifies who this character is and what he means to so many. It is his ultimate sacrifice that shows us what love and hope truly are, and while we are not able to take on Kylo Ren and the First Order or send an astral form of ourselves across the galaxy, we can learn from our mistakes, believe in ourselves, and stand up for what is right, in spite of overwhelming odds. That is why Luke’s confrontation with the First Order on Crait is the most powerful moment in the sequel trilogy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},"publish_date":"April 16,
